A NOTE FROM THE AUTHOR

This is my first Swift project. I started it because I moved from Windows to
macOS and lost access to ScreenToGif — a tool I relied on daily — and could
not find a comparable native replacement on Mac.

The code almost certainly has rough edges: patterns that a seasoned Swift or
macOS developer would do differently, missed Swift concurrency best practices,
AppKit quirks handled in suboptimal ways, and corners that were cut to get
something working. I am fully aware of this and genuinely welcome it.

If you spot something worth improving — architecturally, idiomatically, for
performance, for correctness, or just for clarity — please open an issue or
pull request and tell me. Constructive criticism is not just tolerated here,
it is actively encouraged. This project exists partly as a learning exercise,
and the best way to learn is to have experienced people point at the code and
say "here is a better way."

Thank you for taking the time to look at this.
